dct_title_s: The Nile and its western affluents, between the Albert Nyanza on the south, and the Sobat on the north [cartographic material] : founded on the astronomical observations, bearings and distances, of John Petherick, Esqr. as well as numerous other documents / constructed by John Arrowsmith. (geotiff)
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. "Mr. Petherick's Routes, as well as those of his Agents (Mussaad & Awat), are Coloured [red.]" Discharge of Nile, Gazelle, and Sobat rivers (cubic feet per second) in 1863 is shown. Includes table: Heights [of stations] determined from the temperature of the boiling point of water, observed by Mr. Petherick. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 35, (1865), pp. 289-300; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.35 1865
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Streett. ; 1865.
